<font color="#FF0000">A  VIETNAM VETERAN'S PROTEST</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec  2 23:37:19 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I have read all the posts in this section on protest.<br><br>
I respect those who personally chose to protest the Vietnam War but did not judge those whose personal choices resulted in combat. A debate of choices is the essence of democracy as guaranteed by the Constitution. I would be honored to debate those individuals.<br><br>
I do not respect those whose uninformed moral high ground judgement of those who fought in the Vietnam War is the essence or justification of their protest. No matter what examples are given in support of their position, the reception given to returning Vietnam War combatants by such minded people is validation of their lack of respect for the Constitution and the democratic process. These people are not worthy adversaries in debate.<br><br>
I am a Vietnam Veteran, and you may consider this my protest.   
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


